  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CanHoldContext, HasAssignmentContext<Lecture,Placement,AbstractCriterion.ValueContext>, Criterion<Lecture,Placement>, ExtendedInfoProvider<Lecture,Placement>, InfoProvider<Lecture,Placement>, ModelListener<Lecture,Placement>

    public class InstructorStudentHardConflict
extends InstructorStudentConflict
    Instructor student conflicts. This criterion penalizes cases when an instructor (of a class) is attending some other class as a student and there is a conflict between the two classes. Also, there is no alternative for the student class (the conflict cannot be sectioned away).
    To enable instructor student conflicts, set solver parameter Global.LoadStudentInstructorConflicts to true. Also student course requests should be used in this case (to be able to match an instructor external id to a student external id).
    Hard instructor student conflicts are weighted by Comparator.InstructorHardStudentConflictWeight.
    Version:
    CourseTT 1.3 (University Course Timetabling)
